\begin_layout Standard
SM is a theory of gauge symmetry in the framework of Quantum Field Theory
 (QFT).
 Its three forces correspond to the following symmetry: SU(3)xSU(2)xU(1).
 Each symmetry is accompanied by a number of conserved quantities, and one
 of the quantities that we are familiar with is the electric charge in electroma
gnetism.
 SU(3) corresponds to a strong force, which is described by quantum chromodynami
cs (QCD) under SM, which explains and predicts the matter and force inside
 protons, neutrons, and other similar particles.
 SU(2)xU(1) describes weak and electromagnetic forces, collectively referred
 to as electroweak force, which can be described by quantum electrodynamics
 (QED).
 Their symmetry breaking produces massive W, Z and massless photon.
 They explain the phenomenon of electromagnetics and atomic decay.
