\begin_layout Standard
The fermions in SM are spin-1/2 particles that can be divided into two broad
 categories: leptons and quarks.
 Both leptons and quarks have 3 generations each.
 There are two kinds of particles under each generation.
 Different generations have the same properties except for the different
 masses.
